# From a conversation with Gemini

/* 
The goal is maximizing lactic acid sourness without breakdown

November 13, 2025

# https://gemini.google.com/app/e47193cd35efa43c
*/

starter:
  whole_wheat
  water
  hydration = 100%

grind ^ 4g:
  hard_red = leaven.hard_red + dry.hard_red
  prairie_gold = leaven.prairie_gold + dry.prairie_gold

leaven:
  starter = 1 * _part
  hard_red = 1 * _part
  prairie_gold = 1 * _part
  _part
  water
  total_flour = 10%
  hydration = 100%

wet:
  leaven
  cold_water
  honey = 5%
  olive_oil = 5%
  yogurt = 5%

dry:
  hard_red
  prairie_gold
  vwg = 3%
  hard_red = prairie_gold
  chickpea_flour = 7%
  yeast = 0.2%
  salt = 2%

dough:
  wet
  dry
  total_flour = 200 * 1
  hydration = 80%

/****** Notes

Third attempt, hoping for lower density.

Changes:
* use ice water
* add a little yeast
* knead with the KA until about 72F or 10 minutes
* measure rise from end of kneading.
* use the proofer set for 78F
* prepare leaven overnight?

November 18


Results:

* 85% hydration is too high.

******/


/*
Method and Suggested Timeline

Step 1: Levain Preparation 

Goal: Build a warm, active, high-hydration levain to maximize lactic
acid content upon mixing.

Action: Feed your whole wheat starter at 100% hydration (1:1:1 or
1:2:2 ratio).

Temperature: Let it ripen at a warm temperature (75F to 78F / 24C to
25.5C) until it is very active and bubbly (4–6 hours). The levain is
ready when it is dome-shaped, bubbly, and passes the float test (4–6
hours).

Step 2: Mixing and Autolyse Protection

Goal: Mix all ingredients immediately to activate the protease
inhibitors (salt, yogurt) and protector (oil).

Mixing: Mix the cold water with the salt, honey, olive oil, and
yogurt. Add the flour blend and the ripe levain. Mix until a shaggy
mass forms.

Rest: Cover and rest for 30 minutes.

FDT Target: Aim for a Final Dough Temperature (FDT) around 72F (22C).

Step 3: Bulk Fermentation (Warm & Controlled)

Goal: Push the temperature and time to generate lactic acid while
protecting the gluten.

Ambient Temp: Place the dough in a warm environment: 75F to 78F (24C
to 25.5C).

Folds: Perform 3 sets of coil folds or gentle stretch-and-folds
during the first 90 minutes.

Timing: Total Bulk Fermentation: 3 to 3.5 hours (Approximate).

CRITICAL Indicator: Stop bulk fermentation when the dough has
increased in volume by 30% to 40% and passes the finger-poke test
(springs back slowly, leaving a small dent).

Step 4: Shaping and Cold Proofing

Goal: Set the final shape and stop enzyme activity.

Action: Shape the dough gently into a tight log and place it
seam-down in the oiled Pullman pan.

Proofing: Cover the pan (or put the lid on) and place it immediately
into the refrigerator (38F to 40F / 3C to 4C).

Duration: Cold Proof for 8 to 16 hours.

Check: The dough should rise to 1 to 1.5 inches (2.5 to 4cm) below
the top rim of the pan.

Step 5: Baking

Preheat: Preheat oven to 425F (218 C)

Cold Bake: Place the cold pan (with the lid on) into the preheated
oven.

Bake Time: 30–35 minutes with the lid on.

Reduce heat to 375F (190C), remove the lid, and continue baking for
another 15–25 minutes.

Doneness: Pull the loaf when the internal temperature reaches 205F
to 210F (96C to 99C).

Cooling: Immediately remove the loaf from the pan and cool
completely on a wire rack for at least 2 hours before slicing.

*/

